<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<recipe>
    <name>Ghirardelli Double Chocolate Cookies </name>
    <indexCharacter>G</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Preheat the oven to 300 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg, and the vanilla extract. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, ground cocoa and backing powder. Gradually fold the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture. Fold in the white chips. Using 2 tablespoons, drop the dough onto baking sheets in 1-inch balls, 3 inches apart. Bake for 16 to 18 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes on the baking sheets, then transfer to wire racks to cool completely. Let stand 30 minutes before serving.</instructions>
